<ContentPage
  title="Privacy Policy — What We Collect (Almost Nothing) | LazyTools"
  description="LazyTools processes everything in your browser: your files and inputs are never uploaded. This policy covers the little we do touch — anonymous page analytics and server logs."
  heading="Privacy Policy"
  updated="July 9, 2026"
>
  <p>
    <strong>Plain-English summary:</strong> anything you type into a tool or any file you process stays on your
    device — we never receive it, so we can't store, sell or leak it. The only data we handle is anonymous
    traffic analytics (via cookies, like most websites) and the standard technical logs any web host keeps.
  </p>

  <h2>1. What we never collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>The values you type into tools, the files you process, and any results — all processing happens locally in your browser (<a href="/how-it-works/">how it works</a>).</li>
    <li>Accounts, names, or email addresses — there is no sign-up, and we hold no customer data.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. What we do collect</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Anonymous traffic analytics.</strong> We use analytics cookies to count page views and understand which tools are useful — the standard way most websites evaluate traffic. This records the page URL, referrer, browser type and approximate region — never your identity, and never your tool inputs or files. See the <a href="/cookies/">cookie statement</a> for details.</li>
    <li><strong>Server logs.</strong> Our hosting provider (Namecheap) keeps standard web-server logs (IP address, requested URL, timestamp) for security and operations, retained for a limited period.</li>
    <li><strong>Anonymous ratings (when enabled).</strong> If you rate a tool, we store only the tool name and the star value — no IP address, no identifier, no cookie.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>3. Legal bases and your rights (GDPR/CCPA)</h2>
  <p>
    We process the minimal data above under legitimate interest (operating and improving a free service). Since we
    hold no accounts and no customer data, most data-rights requests (access, deletion, portability) have nothing
    to act on — but you can always <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> with any privacy question or concern, and you
    can block or clear analytics cookies in your browser at any time without affecting the tools.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Third parties</h2>
  <p>
    We do not sell or share data with advertisers. The only third parties involved are our hosting provider and
    our analytics provider, both bound by their own privacy commitments. If this ever changes (for example, if ads
    are introduced), this policy and the site will say so clearly first.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We'll update the "Last updated" date above whenever this policy materially changes, and summarize changes in
    plain language.
  </p>
</ContentPage>
